.SH "NAME"
App::Yath::Plugin::ShareDirDist \- A prove plugin that works with File::ShareDir::Dist
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.07
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\& % yath \-p ShareDirDist
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This plugin sets the override for File::ShareDir::Dist based on
the current directory name, if there is a \f(CW\*(C`share\*(C'\fR directory.  It
assumes that the directory name is the same as the dist name.  This
may not be the case, but it happens to be the convention that I use.
.SH "CAVEATS"
.IX Header "CAVEATS"
As of this writing, Test2::Harness and App::Yath are still
\&\fBexperimental\fR and can change at any time.  Documentation is sparse.
Obviously use this plugin at your own risk.
